article.headline: Oral Roberts 71, Austin Peay 59
article.story: TULSA, Okla. -- Steven Roundtree scored a game-high 24 points and Michael Craion snagged a double-double to boost Oral Roberts over Austin Peay 71-59 on Saturday night. Craion scored 12 points and pulled down 11 rebounds to help the Golden Eagles (2-2) turn a 29-28 lead at halftime into a comfortable win. Roderick Pearson Jr. added 11 points and Dominique Morrison 10 as Oral Roberts made 24 of 58 tries from the field. Tyshwan Edmondson scored 14 points to lead three players in double figures for the Governors (0-3). Will Triggs added 11 and Josh Terry 10. The Governors shot 22 for 60 from the field.
